Mandela in the new film of Clint Eastwood, interpreted by Morgan Freeman
The South Africans claim that the new Hollywood film, Invictus: the Ungeschlagene " shows the world much about the country, their fight and victories, although some critics say that the roles played by the actor.
The story speaks of sports, racial relations and Nelson Mandela.
The tireless campaigner against the racist apartheid regime in South African Republic and its first black president, Nelson Mandela, is the American actor Oscar, Morgan Freeman.
Freeman said that Mandela, 91 years, asked him in the film.
Another important role it plays Matt Damon.
I said to him: " If you play, I will have to have access to you.
The zweiundsiebzigjährige actors, the price for his role in the received Milion dollar baby of Clint Eastwood located in the middle of the leader of the movement for the abolition of slavery, which ended slave, a fictional US president, and even God in the film Evan Almighty but never someone who is still alive and, for many people is as important as Mandela.
The former South African statesman was spent 27 years in prison for his hard work in favour of the end of apartheid in South African Republic.
He was released in 1990 and became president of the country for four years.
In 1993 he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize.
Invictus is a Latin word meaning unbeaten and it is the title of a poem by the English author William Ernest Henley, published in 1875.
The challenge was to speak as he
The film tells the true story of the joint efforts of Nelson Mandela and the captain of the South African rugby team, Francois Pienaar, leading to the country. The new President Mandela knows that his country resteencore and always divided racially and economically after apartheid.
He Believes that is able to unite his people through sport and decides to unite the rugby players, the outsiders, in the world.
The South African team fails to reach the World Cup in 1995.
Freeman worked for several years to bring the history of Mandela on the cinema screens.
He had no other goal than to play this role in these as closely as possible to bring the reality, said Freeman.
The biggest challenge was, of course, so to speak, as he.
The actor said that if he and the world leaders would be in the same area, had tried to meet with Mandela, dinner with him, to be behind the scenes before his speech.
The most important thing was for him to shake Mandela's hand.
I realized that when I shake hands, I recover your energy, it is transmitted and I had the feeling of how you feel, he said.
It is important for me to try to become a different person.
Matt Damon plays in the film François Pienaar, the captain of the national rugby team, in which there is a majority of white players.
The actor said he had six months to prepare for a role in the harsh world of rugby.
It was a big surprise For him, when finally met For the first time with Pienaar at home.
I remember when I come to the door of the house, he opened and the first thing I said to Francois Pienaar in my life was: ' in the film I look much higher ".
Despite the obvious differences between the characters of the players and their real models, under the leadership of the director Eastwood received positive opinions and there is even talk of ambitions for the Oscars.
The film critic of the Daily Variety, Todd McCarthy summed up his assessment in these words: " This was a very good story, a film very well done. "
In the film on the website rottentomatoes. com, Invictus received 76 percent of positive assessments.
The secret of the splendour on Norway resolved: the Russians have tested a missile
Norway was a ray of effect of unknown origin.
The Russian Ministry of Defence has acknowledged that yesterday was tested near the Norwegian border an intercontinental ballistic missile.
The launch failed again. the missile, " Bulava " which was originally to be the pride of the Russian army is becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
His presence repeated tests of the rocket has not had the desired effect on the success of the test flights.
Bulavá, in Most cases, it was flying or there was damaged in the air.
In Russian newspapers speak of " Bulava " as " a missile that did not fly. "
A missile that flies, but do not
This 13th test took place at the beginning.
Only at the end of the flight that there was new damage to the apparatus.
Presumably the engine broke in the third stage of the rocket that exploded.
This time, " Bulava " was launched from the nuclear submarine Dmitry Donskij U boat, which under the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missile launched from a boat that is moving and submerged
That is why It is likely that the mysterious light caused by an unspecified fliegendes object on Northern ways the damaged " Bulava. "
The Norwegians have also since the first moment not doubt that it is a Russian rocket.
The generals argue that this time, we cannot talk of failure.
The first two stages of the rocket fell and affected by the accident was only the third.
In the previous cases were damaged the engines in the first stage.
Although none of the test launches went completely without error, the direction of the Ministry of Defence only six out of thirteen were unsuccessful.
The success of almost 50 per cent full of optimism to the generals and it is claimed that the " Bulava " will fly again without problems and even will take up to ten a total weight of 1.15 tonnes.
