Hyundai has listened to the unions and cancels all overtime
The direction of the car factory in Nošovice agreed with the unions to cancel all overtime.
It is precisely because of the frequent extra work, the unions have declared a state of emergency strike on Monday.
The spokesman confirmed the car factory Hyundai, Petr Vanek.
The management, however, wants to agree with the unions on a Saturday worked this year.
We cannot renounce our production plan, it is essential, that is why We proposed voluntary overtime on Saturday, 19 December knowing that there would be two teams, said Vaněk.
The site Sedmička. cz wrote that the company has offered a bonus of 400 CZK employees who would be part of the team on Saturday.
The staff also received for the Saturday class of 28 November.
According to The company decided to change the way to motivate their employees in exchange for overtime.
Either they receive the supplement for hours, or they can take a free day on 28 December and extend their aindiqué Vaněk.
In addition, all employees present on Saturday will receive compensation for the costs of transport and for their lunch.
Given the fact that overtime were the most urgent and the warmest in the comments and complaints of trade unionists and last week, the production has the management yesterday afternoon decided to cancel all overtime for the month of December, Vank.
The staff of the car factory were forced to work Until last week, practically every day two hours in addition to their eight hours.
The unions cancel the strike after signing of the agreement.
Further negotiations between the management of the car factory and trade unionists must take place on Friday afternoon.
The trade union leader Petr Kuchař said on Wednesday that if they are to meet the demands of some and can sign a joint document that they are prepared to lift the strike.
The situation in the car factory has deteriorated last week, on Wednesday, when approximately 400 employees spontaneously went on strike because of overtime.
They also protested against the poor conditions of payment and alleged harassment.
The direction that employees had to work overtime to meet the requirements of production of cars.
Trade unionists in his declaration of emergency by strike on Monday, also demanded that any of the employees, who last Wednesday the production, with no sanctions.
The unions are asking the company to reduce the time spent in overtime to a minimum.
In addition, they want this year for this work remuneration of 5,000 kroner.
The car factory in Nošovice Hyundai now employs 2,000 people.
In the series production was launched last year in November.
It has produced around 80,000 vehicles until September of this year, with a production capacity of 200,000 cars per year.
Czech discovery: a substance that operates on the HIV virus
The team of Czech and German scientists test new combinations that can slow the spread of HIV in the body.
The main advantage of improved this substance is the fact that it is also the viruses that are resistant to drugs.
In some cases This is more important than the fact that the link is not as effective in a common variant of the virus, as well as some drugs already available.
The disease AIDS can be cured until now.
However, It can prolong the lives of patients through a mixture of drugs that prevent the replication of the HIV virus in the body.
However, their use has a series of side effects.
If the replication of the virus were also has the development of so - called resistant viruses; against the medicines are no longer effective.
The work of the experts of three institutes of the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic, the VŠCHT Prague and the University of Heidelberg opens the way the resistance of the virus.
They have shown that the substances called metalocarboranes act on the protein responsible for the spread of the HIV virus.
The metalocarboranos are compounds of boron, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt.
These compounds are blocking the spread of the virus in a different way of all drugs used today, and so they can solve the problem of resistance.
In The work of the scientists to discover new substances " improved ", on the basis of their knowledge of the molecular mechanism of its Molekularmechanismus their attachment to the virus.
The metalocarboranes have a unique three - dimensional structure: two cages poliedros composed of atoms of boron, hydrogen and carbon are united by and through a metal atom, in this case the cobalt.
A virus traitor and resilient.
The HIV protease is a protein of the HIV virus, which is essential to the life cycle of the virus.
Without the division of HIV, there is the fragmentation of the HIV virus and not create mature and infectious particles of the virus.
If we stop the HIV protease, stop the spread of the virus in the body of the patient, the scientists in a press release issued by the Institute of organic chemistry and biochemistry of the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic.
In an article published in the scientific journal Journal of Medicinal Chemistry, scientists describe a series of combinations where two pairs of cages (see table) are united by a short link, which is then systematically amended.
A little weaker, but more reliable.
The evidence of The effect of this series of substances against the HIV protease has been tested in test tubes and its variants resistant, obtained from patients with HIV.
The impact of the Metalokarborane in the common variant of the enzyme is not as strong as on the clinically used medicines, but they do not lose their effect on the Resistentvarianten, against which the medicines are often ineffective.
The unique effect mechanism and its other properties, such as the biological and chemical stability, low toxicity and the possibility of other chemical changes are compounds to interesting for research, on the development of effective drugs against HIV, says Pavlína Řezáčová, head of the laboratory of structural biology of the Institute of organic chemistry and biochemistry and molecular genetics of the Institute of the Academy of Sciences.
