This is not ideal.
On the other hand, we are pleased to get at least this.
I believe that this is the path that we must now follow said Kalovský.
But the Ministry of Health does not want to change the procedure of vaccination against Pneumokokken.
At the moment I do not think at all, said his spokesman Vlastimil Sršeň.
The voluntary vaccination has its disadvantages, say doctors.
The Hana Cabrnochová, president of the Society of paediatricians, acknowledges that a voluntary vaccination has its drawbacks.
If all children were vaccinated, it could consider a reduction of renewals of vaccinations " in the situation where the vaccine costs such a sum I understand the decision making voluntary vaccination, " said Cabrnochová.
The experts expect that from next year, more than 80 percent of young parents will vaccinate their babies.
The Vaccination against Pneumokokken is a big change also because as the first vaccination in children which is funded by the health insurance and not the state.
The insurance companies should spend the money for the prevention, so that they save for further treatment, explains Cabrnochová.
Doctors have to buy the vaccine for themselves.
This is a concern of the practical paediatricians, the purchase of vaccines.
