The achievement gap has actually increased between 2007 and 2009, from 53 to 58 points.
The progress of African - Americans in the Achtklässler remained essentially the same, he was a statistically significant point from 245 to 244.
The average score of white was not included in the results of the test, because the sample size was not large enough.
