For fifty years, their fate was uncertain.
When searching the database of the Louvre Florent Heintz discovered that this panel was part of a " succession Emile Zola " opened in 1903, a year after the death of the author of " Thérèse Raquin " and the fresco " Rougon - Macquart ".
