From his exile in Costa Rica, returned on 21 September and took refuge in the Brazilian embassy.
If it is, he will be arrested for the crime of " high treason justice, according to the government.
The de facto President Roberto Micheletti has managed to organise a presidential election on 29 November to replace Mr Zelaya.
Porfirio Lobo was elected during the controversial ballot recognized by the United States but disputed by Latin American countries such as Venezuela, Argentina or Brazil.
Three days later, Congress voted overwhelmingly against the return of Mr Zelaya to power until the end of his mandate on 27 January.
