So far it has not received a response, it says.
The ministry said on Saturday not to the accusations and pointed out that will be in the Committee of Inquiry of the Bundestag, which formed next Wednesday.
Dream worlds
Some people see, awake, images and hear voices that others do not see or hear.
Not only in the case of the mentally ill and drug addicts fade the boundaries between fantasy and reality.
While happens during sleep, everything is in order.
When we are lying in our dark rooms, we can do without hindrance to the wildest fantasies.
However, awake, experienced dream, hears and sees things that others do not hear in the modern Western world as to be crazy or drugged, or at least as.
But Such images and voices arise not only in the mentally ill or under the influence of drugs.
Blame our imagination: the same neural processes that enable us to design houses, paint pictures or write novels, but that the boundaries between the dream, madness and reality.
The states of consciousness alert modified can appear in the most diverse forms, in the best case we call them visions, and at worst madness.
But even if the trigger and effect differ, the visions of the mystical Hildegard von Bingen, the experiences of the prophet of the new Age Carlos Castaneda, the psychosis and hallucinations similar processes.
Hallucinations or delusions, if the balance of the neural messenger substances of communication in the brain - especially the dopamine, serotonin and noradrenaline is disrupted and the interaction between different parts of the same.
Complex hallucinations and wahnhafte thoughts are very often during a schizophrenic psychosis.
The gravity has no power over him
The relationship between madness and dream has occupied philosophers and doctors Since ancient times.
Aristotle realised hallucinations as a form of the dream in the state, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of modern psychiatry, found in 1861, a " great similarity between the madness to Sigmund Freud the dream was " a psychosis, with all the absurdities, composed ".
It is the autumn of 2001, when Henning T. transformed into a character.
His body is in two dimensions and scandalously colourful.
The gravity no longer has power over him, is floating near the ceiling.
He feels a kick.
Behind him, figures of demons with wings, with red as blood, showing teeth.
They are pursuing, with heavy boots and flameantes, cast against the walls, he feels the pain throughout the body.
Voices the walls and radio.
It can no longer bear the voices that insult and offend.
Henning T. snaps two cables from the stereo, knotet attached to a noose and consolidating them hooks in the ceiling.
It is rising on a loudspeaker and sets the noose around the neck.
The.
The rope was.
What you will serve as a lesson, the voices in a chorus that the tímpanos, sees the clinic and do you cure! "
Today is Henning T. 40 years old, he has seen six acute psychosis, the last 2 years ago, the first in nearly 20 years.
It was triggered by LSD.
His diagnosis is schizoaffektive paranoid psychosis, moreover, it is, he takes medication, against The depression, mania, schizophrenia.
He has learned to live with his illness, he is married for three years.
In the psychosis I have experienced the most terrible fear and deepest despair, he says.
The illusions are a cruel reality
Approximately one percent of the population suffers at least once in a life of schizophrenia; in psychiatric clinics is the most common illness after the depression.
In a crisis of schizophrenia, people can no longer make the difference between the internal and the outside world, they are in a state of anxiety that can lead to hallucinations, delusions of grandeur, megalomania, or persecution.
Particularly widespread is the hearing voices: voices that give orders, or.
Also optical hallucinations are not rare.
The person concerned is no longer able to separate what is trivial, the brain can ausfiltern not no longer filter the disturbing signals, awareness is awash with impressions.
As the dream, the psychosis opens the floodgates for a flood of ideas and fantasies that come from the deeper layers of conscience.
The perception of reality in the climate is focused on the subject, says Professor Thomas Fuchs, head of the department of Psychiatry in the Universitätsklinikum Heidelberg.
The schizophrenic is in the middle of the situation, everything has an importance to him.
At the same time it is in a passive role, it is a dream, overwhelmed by events and cannot act on them actively.
That is why the schizophrenic often feel threatened, controlled and manipulated.
In general it is not possible to adjust the reality to them, the illusions are a cruel reality, wake up is excluded.
Once seen in the life of a hallucinations To have
Unlike in the dream, according to Fuchs, " the sensory and spatial structure of reality that is perceived in the psychosis, basically. "
The thoughts and hallucinations are based on reality, the alienation of the experience takes place in a real framework.
Why does exactly our brains antics, researchers are still puzzle.
Exceptional conditions can bring everyone to lose the perception of reality, according to Fuchs.
But not all people develop a psychosis.
There seems to be a genetic predisposition to schizophrenia, but studies on twins have shown that the genes are not the only determinants.
Researchers assume that those affected suffer brain damage.
We suspect that the neuronal maturation of the brain is affected at an early stage of development, for example by a viral illness of the mother during pregnancy, explained Fuchs.
But it remains a mystery, as the disruption of the neural system, occurs and the fact that it is not for many years.
Environmental factors also play a role - stress or a traumatic experience can be a trigger of psychosis, if there is a predisposition.
Similarly, the hallucinogenic drugs can trigger psychosis, since they intervene in the transmitter system.
When our brains
This is crazy, Psychotiker suffer from their hallucinations and says Professor of psychology Erich Kasten of Lübeck is that the order to get rid of them, while others pay for drugs that allow them to obtain.
The perception pleasant or unpleasant illusions is often just a question of The point of view.
Kasten collects for ten years reports of hallucinations and related phenomena, last year, he has his results in the book " the unreal world in our head. "
The hallucinations are among the typical effects of psychosis, but also an impressive number of many other diseases.
These include mental disorders, such as Border Line or depression often diseases such as migraine, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis and Alzheimer's disease and head injuries.
It is surprising that in certain conditions even the brain of healthy people is subject to hallucinations.
The hallucinations, according to Kasten, consist of fragments of memories that normally are repressed.
They take form when the areas of the brain that process sensory perceptions are hiperactivas or little; when our brains hot, but also when there is a lack of stimulation.
The drugs can trigger this state in The same way that the brain damage or a psychosis.
But also the lack of stimulus, stress, the evil of love or other mental states.
In recent studies have been up to a third of those polled said that at least once in the life of a hallucinations.
In the summer of 2005 is Sarah K. 16 years old, she lives in a small town in Mecklenburg - Western Pomerania and it goes to the school.
A normal girl.
If it were not for the images and voices.
During the break, it can happen that a schlaksiger boy with long, dark hair and the floor.
When he replies, take a look at the classmates surprisingly - no one else sees or hears this boy.
They believe that the timid girl is a ensoñadora a little strange, but Sarah K. not dreaming, it is certain.
It is, hear and see the boy as she sees and hears the girl who is sitting in the bank.
They can feel his presence even, at least for moments.
It is a pleasant feeling, they like the boys.
Am I crazy? , asks them sometimes.
But she knows that this boy and the other visions are not real and they will disappear again.
At night, the appearances are alarming.
The visions are Often a burden.
When it is in class sometimes it can follow the course because the professor in their eyes and ears is presenting a new colleague, while for is invisible to others and that the mathematical equations.
At night, the appearances are alarming.
While waiting in the dark room to reach the dream, which is far too little and too late, they often cannot distinguish whether she is awake or dreaming, if the images they see, the grimaçants or the girl with cuts in arms and legs, with the bleeding before their eyes open or closed.
Let me in peace, they are the characters.
Parents and friends told them nothing, which would be crazy.
Autumn 2009. Sarah K. is now 20 years.
Approved last year selectivity and lives with her boyfriend.
A year ago the hallucinations have stopped.
Since it came into contact via the Internet with the psychologist Kasten, she knows that she is not crazy.
The madness is also a work of art of despair.
According to Kasten, When a person is isolated socially or suffers a restriction of stimulus, it is very likely that after a certain time.
I suspect that the brain is underemployed, and even for his Unterhaltung.
Sarah K., single girl, was of little fear of other children and often played alone.
Their hallucinations began when she learned to 13, that the man she called Daddy, since it was in age, was not his real father.
As visual and acoustic hallucinations the same brain areas that are active in the the real impressions and noise, it is affected as Sarah K. difficult to distinguish between vision and reality. " every experience takes place in the brain, the reality is formed from there.
The hallucinations are also images that form in the brain, which is why they seem so real. "
Also night dream images of digesting caste as a form of hallucinations.
The hallucinations of healthy people do not differ fundamentally from those of an acute psychosis.
Unlike the schizophrenic, mentally healthy people are able to recognize their views as unrealistic.
That is why Kasten advises his patients to cherish the hallucinations as a special skill.
Border state between dream and hallucinations
In our world too focused on the conscience what experiences imaginary tend to generally patologizarse, says Michael Schmidt - Degenhard, professor in Heidelberg and chief doctor of the clinic psychiatry and psychotherapy of Florence Nightingale hospital in Düsseldorf.
A psychosis is a heavy, painful but which also contains something positive, creative - the madness is a work of art of despair.
Schmidt - degenhard has investigated the so - called oneirismo, a particular form of awareness, which is perceived as a dream.
The experienced oniroïdes are very complex semi - dimensional, detailed Quasi dreams, which are seen as real by the lives and that it cannot differentiate the.
The state of consciousness oniroïde occurs during a trauma or in extreme situations of illness, for example in patients with polirradiculoneuropatía, experiencing a motor paralysis.
According to Schmidt - Degenhard, when a person is threatened by a loss of self and the world, due to a total disability and sustainable to move, it replaces the real situation very dangerous for its own imaginary world, the reality is, says rapier hard.
A kind of border state between dream and hallucinations.
As it is not possible to overcome the situation in reality, a change in the world, but the real situation is represented in the imagination.
An intensive form of Sinn Foundation and meaning, in an intolerable situation, which allows people to design their own ability, not submerged in nothing of the loss of consciousness.
Everything is real, even later in the memory
Also The art historian Peter Cornelius Classen, describes his experiences in his book " change of heart " as a rescue action of the soul.
He is 49 years, when his consciousness for a trip of several days after the operation of a heart valves with a heart transplant included, while his body was sentenced to immobility in the intensive care.
Claussen visited another in a selbstgeschaffene world, other times and places: he saw himself as bettlägerigen, old man, boarded a Zugsanatoriums, a robot guarding his health.
He lives in the early Middle Ages of nobles who drugs from blood.
He was abducted by a Greek on the motorcycle in his home country, surfing with his hospital bed in the Alps and meeting a Korean mafia.
He is completely in the imagined, everything is real, even later in the memory.
These internal travel For Claussen fundamentally different from any dream.
Dream is a different situation, he describes his experience.
On the contrary, the memories from mental travel are extremely clear and very detailed even years later.
They are much more clear and more intensive than the real experiences.
The intensity of this experience the horizon of the rest of our other everyday experience, adds the psychiatrist Schmidt - Degenhard.
Ultimately, the oneirismo, psychosis, hallucinations and drugs show how fragile our internal figures of external reality in the guards.
Any change of the state of conscience, summarizes the psychologist Kasten, " can lead to a distortion of what we call reality. "
An experience which might also be enriching.
