Michelin and Fesvial together for the use of the Helms
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, with the cooperation of the Spanish Foundation for road Safety (Fesvial) , has launched a campaign to promote the use of helmets, mainly among the younger motorcyclists, reported today the two structures.
This initiative is to raise awareness of the importance of the helmet, since it is the only element of protection to avoid injuries to the head, or even death in the event of an accident in two wheels.
Michelin indicated that this campaign is part of his commitment to road safety, which " goes beyond the design and manufacture of products always safer " and said that it also contributes to this objective by other actions educational and informative.
This new campaign to promote the helmet use on the motorcycle, under the slogan ' to be or not to be ', will have a first phase in which posters will be distributed in more than 500 motorcycle workshops, in order to achieve the widest dissemination.
Finally, Michelin stressed that road safety " is a constant concern " for the company, because as a manufacturer of tyres for two - wheeled vehicles, one of its main objectives is to develop products always safer.
The sale of light commercial
After almost two years, the market for light commercial vehicles are beginning to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9,425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of declines, according to figures from the employers of manufacturers Anfac and sellers Ganvam.
The good thing, However, since the reference for comparison, the month of November 2008, was particularly bad, with a decrease of 60% on the previous year.
Consequently, despite the surge in the last month, the the 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
Since January, 95.853 units have been sold together all vehicles that make up the category of light commercial vehicles (derived from passenger cars, pick up, vans, vans and light trucks/chassis.
Furthermore, have not gone away the clouds that most affect their demand, because although they are also purchased by individuals, most of the purchases are made by small and medium - sized enterprises, which pay in almost 100% of cases through external funding.
So in addition to the restrictions of the tap closed for bank loans, other factors such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the poor economic situation.
In this situation and unlike cars, aid for the purchase of the little used.
In addition to individuals, the self - employed and small businesses that will acquire a commercial slight of up to 3.5 tonnes with a level of CO2 emissions than 160 grams per kilometre, but the number of operations speaks for itself.
Yesterday, since Ganvam to remember the need for the administration to devote special attention to these vehicles and also to the industrial vehicles (trucks and buses) .
The association of dealers predicts a similar to the year 2010 a year, for which estimated a fall in sales (for passenger cars and 4x4s) of 19%.
The emergency brake is now mandatory
As happened with the anti - lock brakes ABS and as will happen with the ESP stability control systems will have to be a compulsory element on European cars.
In fact, They are already mandatory on passenger cars and light commercial vehicles newly registered, while for the rest is set a waiting period until the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to improve the protection of pedestrians, even if, by his way to work, it can also help prevent many rear shocks.
The assistant emergency braking is increasing the pressure on the brakes in the event of an emergency, the system detected by the driver.
But it is not always maintained the pressure until the end.
According to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for car Bosch, a third of the drivers involved in an accident had not come to step on the brakes before the collision, and half of them had not slowed down with full force.
Up to 1,100 accidents
The intervention of the aid, revancha, requires the braking system, reducing the distance that used the car to stop.
According to a study by the EU itself, if all cars were equipped with this type of elements, up to 1,100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be avoided each year.
This reduction would be even more important with greater - it is estimated that the popularization of so - called intelligent emergency braking a disaster on four with injuries would be avoided.
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system that (through a radar or a camera) detects obstacles and warns the driver, in addition to act slightly on the brakes.
If the driver reacts, helps to increase the pressure on the pedal, if necessary.
If it does not react, and although the collision is inevitable, the device is the maximum effort on the brakes in order to minimize the damage.
