How much should be paid according to your profile on Facebook?
Users of Facebook can know the salary they deserve according to his profile, thanks to a new application of Trovit, the search engine with the largest number of real estate, employment and vehicles in Spain.
The tool " How much it? " AngebotenVVPP calculated the salaries of users from more than 140 000 job available Trovit in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where must introduce their profession, years of experience, age and the city where you want to work.
For a week that the application works, the search engine has found that in general the Spanish worker " feels badly paid, " said in a statement the for the product of Trovit, Albert Ribera.
According to the data available Trovità from its search engines in the United Kingdom and France, the Spanish are the worst paid.
A British computer programmer 45,226 euros annual gross and a Frenchman, 31,059, while a Spanish receives 24 000.
In the same way, a driver is 34.247 euros annual net in England, 25 751 in France and in Spain.
According to Trovit, work in Spain is the waiter, with a net 11,592 euros per year; followed by the seller, with 14.725 euros and the worker, with 15,667 euros.
