Their participation in the Champions League has brought reported 476,4 million to Real Madrid and Barça since its creation
The Champions League has become a source of income for clubs, since its birth in 1992.
So much so that Real Madrid and Barcelona since 476.4 million, putting them at the third and fifth place of clubs who have earned the most money in the competition.
The leader of the list is Manchester United.
The leader of the list is Manchester United.
Winning the UEFA Champions League not only brings glory. It is also one of the main sources of income of the big clubs.
So much so that the competition has distributed 5.362,5 million to the 105 teams (12 Spanish) who participated in the event since the creation of the tournament in the season, according to UEFA.
Real Madrid and The F. C. Barcelona have been well from this distribution.
The club was the third of the continent to receive more money for his participation, and the only one, along with AC Milan, which has won the trophy three times.
The Catalan club, the current champion and the last winner of the former European Cup in 1992, is the fifth of the classification.
The list of the lead Manchester United and Bayern Munich, the two teams, in addition, more money for their participation in the last Champions League.
And that, although they have lost against Barça.
On the other hand, Spain is only the third country, by the Champions of League, although it has won more titles than any other (five, while Italy, three of England and Germany two) .
Distribution
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex procedure of distribution of money applied by UEFA.
For this year, the body chaired by Michel Platini plans to win 1,090 million through the Champions League.
This money UEFA will devote 413,1 million for fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs who participated in the preliminary round of classification (including the Atlético de Madrid) received 2.1 million.
In addition, those who have managed to participate received 3.8 million just to be there, in addition to other euros for each party.
There is also a bonus for winning (800,000 euros) and equality (400,000 for each team) . the octavofinalistas will receive three million each; the eight cuartofinalistas, 3.3 million.
The last four teams will each received 4 million.
The champion won 9 million, compared to the 5.2 million finalist.
So, in fixed payments, a club will win at least 7.1 million, and a maximum of 31.2 million.
On the other hand, has pocketed $2.5 million for winning the European Super Cup in August.
But in addition, there are variable payments, which are scheduled for the 337.8 million.
This money is distributed according to the proportional to the value of each television market.
The Spanish market is one of the key, and has four seats.
The champion of the previous year is 40% of the money allocated, 30% for the second, 20% for the third and 10% for the fourth.
The other part will be paid depending on the number of games they play in this year's edition, distributed.
